{{No official name}}
The '''lord''' is a farm-owner and father of [[Arastasia]]. One of his farm hands, [[Dentristus]], was in love with his daughter.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=His lord had a beautiful daughter, Arastasia, with whom he was in love.}}

During a harsh winter, the [[Wintertodt]] was drawn for the north devouring animals and crops,{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=That winter was the Great Winter which drew down the Wintertodt from the north, It proceeded to devour the animals upon the farm and freezing the next year's crops.}} Dentristus vowed to defeat the [[Wintertodt]], and in exchange the lord offered Arastasia's hand in marriage.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=I vow that I will venture into the mountains and destroy the beast so it shall trouble us no more....

...if you succeed I will grant you my daughter's hand in marriage as you will truly be the only man that can make her happy.}} The lord geared Dentristus with his best equipment,{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=Dressed in the Lord's best armour and wielding his most dangerous weapon Destristus started upon his quest.}} though this was not enough and Dentristus would eventually succumb to the Wintertodt's chill.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=Dentristus lay dead before he even saw the Wintertodt}}

